elements.2211.03012_18b4b9e459f0bc168b27168e3d271: In the last few decades, uncertainty quantification (UQ) methods have been used widely to ensure the robustness of engineering designs
elements.2211.03012_62b30e70eee32744021f763609246: This chapter aims to detail recent advances in popular uncertainty quantification methods used in engineering applications
elements.2211.03012_b273c7901195dd516293fce7a6fe5: This chapter describes the two most popular meta-modeling methods for uncertainty quantification suitable for engineering applications (Polynomial Chaos Method and Gaussian Process)
elements.2211.03012_036f3ded9abfc72f2f054078f4bcb: Further, the UQ methods are applied to an engineering test problem under multiple uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_a695008eeb1a74d84774d4956f392: The test problem considered here is a supersonic nozzle under operational uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_fba9ddeb52abbf3c2a46544820cc4: For the deterministic solution, an open-source computational fluid dynamics (CFD) solver SU2 is used
elements.2211.03012_980279c561907c2a8d125869c930f: The UQ methods are developed in Matlab and are further combined with SU2 for the uncertainty and sensitivity estimates
elements.2211.03012_ba922fdfc3bdac6ab3ece832b4135: The results are presented in terms of the mean and standard deviation of the output quantities.
elements.2211.03012_92946736580a87142dff0c910c11d: In industrial applications, during the operation of engineering devices, several properties and parameters of the components change with time
elements.2211.03012_3761d591f6e286a92dd76f82ba0af: The material properties of its components vary continuously due to several operational factors
elements.2211.03012_1b490845df711f0d1e357d3bcc06b: The failure point information of the week components in an industrial application is very useful
elements.2211.03012_fa7ec817e099fb799823cea6929ab: The safety of the engineering device under consideration should always be of utmost concern for the manufacturers while designing the device
elements.2211.03012_1e06a690aee1068063cf869b8c457: Using statistical information, the designer can evaluate the safety margin or make the failure design margin smaller than other components so that the impact of the weak component can be minimized
elements.2211.03012_855bcac46ee57d43420b49ebcc73b: With advancements in computer hardware and numerical algorithms, computational tools are used to design advanced and high-performance engineering components in almost all engineering fields
elements.2211.03012_0f9889df1399a79a9192d52989cab: For example, aircraft, high-speed car manufacturers, sports, naval ship designers, etc., use computational fluid dynamics (CFD) to simulate fluids over the device
elements.2211.03012_81afd5ce6b557e396b9ad16daf205: These computational tools are also used for thermal and structural analysis to simulate and detect faults, cracks, and failure of the devices by almost all industries.
elements.2211.03012_1a753891cee409259cbc195e61d09: Uncertainties are an inherent part of the computing systems concerning real-world applications
elements.2211.03012_f48c681d65e686f73197e6cb03067: Two physical experiments can never produce the same results as several of the system parameters are not known properly and have uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_a2fc52265e0e66ea20b03468ffdb3: When the same system is modeled using computational tools and mathematical equations, the input and system parameters are provided with constant values to predict the results without dealing with the uncertainties in the input parameters
elements.2211.03012_60f917559508a7206cb15cf6f9f21: Almost all aspects of engineering modeling and design are affected by these uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_8cef0a327959165c7be4524012c61: Engineers and researchers have always encountered issues related to uncertainties in terms of design reliability and robustness
elements.2211.03012_660147bd5a6331d16f5d04613ec0a: By understanding sources of uncertainties and quantifying them, one can estimate confidence in the system outputs
elements.2211.03012_7458191e9ea0a4564839f2c13fb1c: In mathematical modeling, uncertainties are usually encountered in initial conditions, boundary conditions, material properties, weather conditions, and manufacturing tolerances.
elements.2211.03012_043d592849feb8d30e9954d7e7d56: Uncertainty Quantification (UQ) is the field of detecting, describing, quantifying, and managing uncertainties in computational designs of real-world systems
elements.2211.03012_72639df5738c2205a6f92e9ed9304: In UQ, the system response is estimated in a stochastic way by combining the deterministic solver with statistical tools
elements.2211.03012_bcd88a2398abd464c2ddbe68acbe2: UQ methods are statistical tools to assess safety margins in the system responses when computer simulations are used to design an engineering device
elements.2211.03012_34213f238f37234cd5d4150951d7f: UQ methods address the problems associated with incorporating system parameters variability and stochastic behavior into systems analyses
elements.2211.03012_2d7f4da48d39d5ab5934071025110: Computer simulations answer what happens when the system under consideration is subjected to a set of input parameters
elements.2211.03012_2d3a3d4f951f8c6e3cccc8bb19092: However, UQ expands this question and answers what will happen when the system is subjected to a range of variability in the input parameters
elements.2211.03012_de8886263226627d0e4903a272b32: UQ combines mathematics, statistics, and engineering
elements.2211.03012_574c32850bd6f14da01184be29c8d: Generally speaking, UQ methods predominantly treat the system to be studied as a closed system (like a black box), and an extensive understanding of the system's inner functioning is not required
elements.2211.03012_6164fc7610da7f2f72b4d3c857950: The UQ methods only need information about the input parameters of the model and model responses to estimate probabilistic model responses
elements.2211.03012_1779fcb5d5182a932c605a353648e: In the recent past, uncertainty quantification and management are considered as significant elements in risk management (the system can fail or be damaged if it does not meet the design targets) of industrial designs
elements.2211.03012_47ba82edd8ad557199f778b7e9c16: Due to the non-intrusive nature of UQ methods, these methods can be adopted easily by researchers and industries from a wide range of engineering, industrial and financial sectors to:
elements.2211.03012_e482cb4b6643c9f0e8f3be226fdab: Understand the uncertainties inherent in the system.
elements.2211.03012_1cb40411d61237e59fede774589ac: Predict system responses concerning uncertain inputs.
elements.2211.03012_6e1b4f7e3bd64f76a5aa7eaae91b4: Quantify confidence in the system responses.
elements.2211.03012_2d1f08e35d596caba3d2e138b3c3d: Find optimal responses concerning a wide range of inputs.
elements.2211.03012_a7f06e6a0582fcc96a87717d83588: Implement probabilistic modeling and design processes.
elements.2211.03012_85a6959536855409b2316b1a41031: Predict parametric sensitivity on the model responses.
elements.2211.03012_14e77df6a480c07ab7ed8a5c9681f: With increasing computational power and simulation techniques, it became possible to make accurate predictions of real-world systems
elements.2211.03012_bf7023b2a8002216919537577ca54: Now the challenges in engineering designs are moved toward predicting system behaviors with respect to uncertainties efficiently
elements.2211.03012_b982db99889e981631037d9c57c63: Traditional UQ methods based on Monte Carlo
elements.2211.03012_2d17b7764d089a79dffddb08177ce: usually need a large number of system evaluations
elements.2211.03012_53cb94013eb75829ed0908da762ca: So these methods are restricted to simplified test cases and for research purposes only
elements.2211.03012_2d923e0d4b4babcf0e7b28737a545: Monte Carlo methods are sampling-based methods, and the convergence rate is very slow
elements.2211.03012_67f3d24d65950544b0c7e22df7f27: ) are needed to predict statistical quantities accurately
elements.2211.03012_27b1c917e2d0c52743090a86e6bb2: Alternatively, the literature proposes several sampling schemes such as Latin Hypercube, Sparse sampling, clustered sampling, and stratified sampling to accelerate the convergence
elements.2211.03012_7e954275c9919a4a06662b8f50725: However, Monte Carlo methods have not gained massive popularity due to their expensive computational cost
elements.2211.03012_6c81a77a6e0d3dd6decb9f99d8afc: For large-scale problems and real-world engineering applications, more recent methods based on machine learning approaches such as Polynomial Chaos Method (PCM)
elements.2211.03012_a965ed779a32427d40fbc34c92dbe: are proposed in literature and are applied to several diverse applications
elements.2211.03012_2afdf574dc389fd9790e712c3d095: Polynomial chaos and Gaussian process models are seen as leading approaches for stochastic and robustness analyses of very complex engineering applications
elements.2211.03012_b1a058913109dc9ec592c4ba976f1: PC-Kriging is a result of combining polynomial chaos and Kriging methods
elements.2211.03012_bce34732ddd6fccb5e7a0de2112cb: These approaches are discussed in detail and are applied to an engineering application in the following sections.
elements.2211.03012_910d4dd966af07ee529f05c2000c8: In order to understand the potential influence of input parameters on system outputs, the Sensitivity Analysis (SA) method is used
elements.2211.03012_9f8f893622315ba8f34a2288ca9cb: Various methods for global sensitivity analysis, such as linear regression and variance-based analysis are discussed for sensitivity estimation
elements.2211.03012_bb111ef8abb2b9df48eae23745e39: A standard method of estimating system responses is using Sobol' indices-based global sensitivity analyses
elements.2211.03012_4e0c0e40e6bb6109ba6c0807f0936: Various meta-modeling methods can compute Sobol indexes, including Monte Carlo, graphical models, Kriging, and support vector machine approaches
elements.2211.03012_9f38c15be86666db4ac518d9c1ec0: In recent years, surrogate models that calculate Sobol' indices have gained considerable attention
elements.2211.03012_d44d99dc5ffb09102a50f9a0ae567: The first step in this approach is to construct a surrogate model using the design of experiments (DOE)
elements.2211.03012_dc43c93bcf8f273943183f0517f06: Furthermore, this surrogate model is used to estimate many model responses in order to compute Sobol' indices
elements.2211.03012_afc3bb97f280ada8ba5d184c07fa3: Computing model responses from surrogate models are also called data-driven approaches, as several combinations of input parameters are used to explore a wide range of input domains.
elements.2211.03012_87c5294e0aaa5f8f5ca40a41964b6: In 1938, Wiener proposed the polynomial chaos method for dealing with Gaussian distributed uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_58143a92cc139ead4f77ddcce48ff: demonstrated the ability to use it with any probability distribution in a detailed analysis
elements.2211.03012_ae812f56e9af63db997861a84e49d: In the last few years, the generalized method has been used in a variety of engineering applications, including computational fluid dynamics, heat transfer, nuclear reactor design, and structural analysis
elements.2211.03012_85b185bf9881e0904d206643546c4: Because adding uncertainties increases the computation required to quantify them, early applications dealt with a limited number of uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_1db5ffce067cfbe48bbcd6c547d27: With increasing uncertainties, the number of simulations required to quantify the uncertainty grows exponentially using the polynomial chaos method
elements.2211.03012_9c56d6c248e13472512f69679bda7: This is referred to as the dimensionality curse
elements.2211.03012_567521170e976a091c4b54095fb91: Numerous improvements have been proposed in literature
elements.2211.03012_f58bfd03c7844c9b6f932ac97c174: to cope with the curse of dimension and move the UQ process forward
elements.2211.03012_8d0dfc28292bee33e23f2bb44c70c: Several researchers also proposed model reduction algorithms (based on principal component analysis) to accelerate the polynomial chaos method.
elements.2211.03012_cf7d7a9d7187f9c32fcba0c25a7a6: Numerous applications have used model reduction approaches
elements.2211.03012_3248122765932e837b87292efd80a: However, these approaches mainly were two steps processes and usually were applied in semi-intrusive ways
elements.2211.03012_de7847e74224a81a1c47864f9ff93: Thus, they were not very straightforward to use for engineering applications where the models can be used as a black-box
elements.2211.03012_373cf159fd2ade630aec8c506a3f3: Several researchers proposed the idea of sparse sampling
elements.2211.03012_3985fdd4f21f6fb371d468b5db667: Using sparse sampling schemes (such as Fejer, Clenshaw-Curtis, Conrod-Patterson), the number of simulations can be reduced to achieve the same accuracy as classical polynomial chaos
elements.2211.03012_0240055c2f53e1d2766b19235f349: Blatman and Sudret proposed a theory of sparse polynomial chaos, based on least angle regression in their paper
elements.2211.03012_afdc33c687aff8acdc6521d14ca94: Based on its principle, this method used a maximum number of polynomial order approximations for a given number of samples and a sparse polynomial chaos expansion (PCE) for a given system response
elements.2211.03012_c1fe5ded1798ceb7e8427f4890e8e: Several other researchers also proposed the more or less similar idea of sparse polynomial chaos using different error minimizing schemes
elements.2211.03012_3a01f71effdb65329adefd0cb1fff: Recently, numerous applications have seen the sparse polynomial chaos approach due to its straightforward usage and faster convergence capability
elements.2211.03012_8d5123074fd3549d945cb8dd305a3: In this section, some fundamental concepts for the polynomial chaos approach are described

elements.2211.03012_1dbfaad8bca00bc722cbab89ac795: Uncertainty Quantification of a Supersonic Nozzle
elements.2211.03012_29b5841229ff2ca57e5b26dc3f338: The UQ is crucial for assuring the results produced by mathematical modeling in engineering applications
elements.2211.03012_0083b2d19c07566be823945dd59d1: The standard deviation or variance can be considered a safety bound or a confidence interval around the mean values
elements.2211.03012_90c656e5741edc88383d589e74bf9: Hence, we apply the methods discussed in the previous sections to an engineering application in this section
elements.2211.03012_28d3b35de3e58030c61433915d445: We analyze the non-ideal supersonic compressible flow within a 2D converging-diverging nozzle shown in Figure
elements.2211.03012_202604a9a5a489b363055f9eea57c: The nozzle is 0.123 m long, with a throat height of 0.0084 m and an inlet height of 0.036 m
elements.2211.03012_a06b2003f8d3de38454623f0560a2: This is a test case provided in SU2 for deterministic CFD simulations
elements.2211.03012_88ba578b9c7bfccc894d276307c06: It has a simple geometry where the flow accelerates from subsonic to supersonic speeds
elements.2211.03012_8bdbf1760ba1824ae2fb79bc33428: It can be used to investigate compressible flows where simple ideal gas laws are not enough to describe thermodynamic behavior properly
elements.2211.03012_4a03ddd63181fd192b3061258eb13: To determine the performance of the nozzle over a wide range of inlet conditions, CFD simulations are first used to confirm its performance
elements.2211.03012_38cd60e1a9e3e1473f7bca7c95c15: Then further CFD simulations are combined with uncertainty quantification methods
elements.2211.03012_50115eb50aa4901ca2c5dee7a069e: Additionally, the uncertainty bounds for the nozzle performance in terms of pressure and Mach number, flow density, and temperature fields along the centerline are evaluated with respect to input uncertainties
elements.2211.03012_1d33bc56bc788d33a8b515cee15a0: They are shown with mean and standard deviation values.
elements.2211.03012_ce6912bfca40f7b79ebfb7f0e0831: Octamethyltrisiloxane (MDM), a pressure-sensitive fluid, is used as a working fluid for analyzing non-ideal supersonic compressible flow inside a converging-diverging (CD) nozzle
